# Security and Restrictions

Mandatory restrictions for implementation.

- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, credentials, or connection URIs.
- Never log passwords, JWTs, or sensitive PII.
- Never skip authentication/authorization checks on protected endpoints.
- Never trust client-provided role or identity when JWT identity is available.
- Never bypass input validation.
- Never place business logic in routes.
- Never perform direct DB-heavy logic in controllers.
- Prefer soft delete (`isDeleted`) for recoverability and auditability.
- Avoid unbounded queries; use pagination and indexes for frequent filters.
- Do not expose stack traces or internal error objects in production responses.
